title: Ramsay helps visiting Vikings sweep Plainsmen
text:
Ramsay helps visiting Vikings sweep Plainsmen By: Uncredited Report Error 
Jasmine Ramsay led the visiting Vincent Massey junior varsity girls with four kills and three aces as the Vikings beat the Crocus Plainsmen 3-0 on Wednesday in the Westman High School Volleyball League. 
Kate Fergusson added five kills and Kalyn Tokaryk had four kills and two blocks as Massey won 25-15, 25-9, 25-15. 
Jordanna Chartrand had five digs and four kills for the Plainsmen. 
In boys’ JV play, Brock Carmichael had eight kills and Matthew Rust had five as Massey (1-0) beat host Crocus 3-0 (25-17, 25-18, 25-9). 
Jared Bridges had nine kills for Crocus (0-2).
